				</div>
				<div style="clear: left;">
															<p> My grandson is the other way around. He is in kindergarden and the teacher doesn't like it because  David doesn't join in playing games with the other kids. He would rather sit and watch, or he doesn't jump and hollor its his turn. The teacher is worried about this, But on the other hand she says he loves to sit and talk to her and other chiildren. Isn't this the time when children are suspose to be interacting on their own level. We can't form them into what we think is right for them.I beleve we make our children grow up to fast these days.</p>
																				</div>
			</td>
