</a></strong></div>
					<div style="clear: both;"></div>
				</div>
				<div style="clear: left;">
															<p>Our children sound very similar. In some ways you were probably both better off for what you didn't know, and didn't expect. One of the things that has saved us until now is that my son's school is a progressive school that doesn't give grades until 7th grade. (He's in 3rd now) Interesting that you chose and were successful with montessori - I would have thougth the lack of structure would be confusing for a child like your son, but it sounds like the freedom allowed him to learn in his own way. </p>
<p>I often tell my son that someday his strengths will be the things that matter at school and in life(like yours a wonderful memory and interest in science, technology and abstract concepts). But right now all he sees is that the other kids can read Harry Potter. </p>
<p>Good for you for helping him find his way.</p>
																				</div>
