															<p>He doesn't have aspergers, or a diagnosis of NLD, but if you took him on a bad day from a few years ago and cranked up the severity level of his issues you could think he did. His affect and his use of language can be a little off, particuarly with new people. When he's comfy he can be quite charming.  I think our intervention, and his other strengths have helped him compensate tremendously. But I know I can' t take my eye off this issue, and I need to shore up his self esteem and social skills before he changes schools, which will certainly challenge him socially.</p>
<p>If you think of any titles let me know! ( or videos, stories about other kids etc.. thanx!)</p>
